Kentucky Derby (1954) | updated= September 9, 2008 }} 'Determine' (1951â€“1972), was an American Thoroughbred race horse. In a racing career which lasted from 1953 through 1955, the California-trained colt ran forty- four times and won eighteen races. His best season was 1954 when he became the first gray horse to win the Kentucky Derby.
